Species Comments: 1st noticed by unfamiliar, high-pitched honking. Slightly smaller than a nearby Canada Goose, with grey body, neck, and head. White patch at base of bright orange beak. bright orange legs/feet. No eye ring, dark eye. Dark splotches on belly. located at approx 39.745086,-104.946333 (via Google Maps).

Swimming in small pond at 39.704083,-105.085734. Swimming with a group of ~90 Canada Geese. Dull pink bill with the white markings at the base of bill. Noticeably thick neck. Strikingly white rump that sat a bit higher in the water than a CG. Feet/legs orange. Back feathers similar in color to CG. Overall size was slightly larger than the CG it was swimming with. Excellent views.
Checklist Comments: no coots seen today, the normal kingfisher not seen either.

Species Comments: Viewed from less than 10 yards at the edge of the small pond that's connected to the lake, pinkish bill, mottled white behind bill, orange legs/feet. Possibly a domestic goose since out of season here.
